This paper is about image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of hierarchical structures in the network, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of multinomial logistic loss and layer parameter compression suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of benchmark datasets and state-of-the-art results suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
